GOVERNOR Babajide Sanwo-Olu is expected to host the inaugural World Alaga Day scheduled to hold on February 22, 2022. The event, which is aimed at preserving Yoruba culture and rebranding traditional ceremonies, will also have in attendance eminent monarchs including the Alake of Egbaland, Oba Aremu Gbadebo and the Olu of Itori, Oba AbdulFatai Akorede. The coordinator of the event, Mrs. Aduke M Sewoniku, who was represented by Mrs Titilayo Adegboye, disclosed this at a press conference in Lagos, according to a statement by the organisers. She was quoted as calling on the federal and state governments to become stakeholders in the upliftment of the traditional culture. However, the inaugural event is expected to be preceded by a health walk, feature seminar, dinner, and an award night. According to Sewoniku, Sanwo-Olu is the grand patron of the Alaga industry in Nigeria and in the Diaspora. The event is expected to bring together not less than 2000 “Alaga” from Lagos, Ogun, Ondo, Oyo, Kogi, Kwara and Osun states.